    "This includes first-impression bias, ideological/theoretical orientation, language, social identity, and prestige biases (Lee et al., 2013; Siler et al., 2015).",
    "Challenges remain in modeling these biases, although some studies are attempting to do so (e.g., Feliciani et al., 2019).",
    "In particular, machine-learning AI techniques are inherently conservative, as they are trained with data from the past.",
    "This could lead to bias when such tools are used to inform current review decisions.",
    "For example, papers from countries that have historically been under-represented in the literature could have a higher rejection rate using AI methods since the reviews may not adequately account for the rising quality of submissions from such regions over time (Checco et al., 2021)."
